00:04:54.430 --> 00:04:57.949
I felt as if I was hearing her heart for the first time.

00:04:58.949 --> 00:05:03.430
It truly reaches the heart and motivates students to action.

00:05:04.709 --> 00:05:06.230
And one brother wrote,

00:05:06.230 --> 00:05:09.189
I am so excited about this new Bible course

00:05:09.189 --> 00:05:11.750
that I am begging Jehovah to hear my prayers

00:05:11.750 --> 00:05:14.990
to be able to conduct progressive studies.

00:05:16.589 --> 00:05:19.110
It was early in 2019 when the writing committee

00:05:19.110 --> 00:05:20.750
took on the amazing project

00:05:20.750 --> 00:05:23.269
to produce a new Bible study tool.

00:05:23.269 --> 00:05:26.069
They assembled a team of writers, designers,

00:05:26.069 --> 00:05:29.069
and consultants to investigate whether we could improve

00:05:29.069 --> 00:05:31.589
the publications that we were then using.

00:05:32.709 --> 00:05:35.230
At the very first discussion session,

00:05:35.230 --> 00:05:37.550
everyone was encouraged to pray often

00:05:37.550 --> 00:05:38.910
about the task at hand,

00:05:38.910 --> 00:05:40.670
to pray when thinking about it,

00:05:40.670 --> 00:05:44.589
when brainstorming with others and when working on it,

00:05:44.589 --> 00:05:47.189
and to respond to the influence of Holy Spirit.

00:05:48.470 --> 00:05:49.829
Why pray so much?

00:05:50.709 --> 00:05:55.189
Proverbs 16 verse three gives the answer.

00:05:56.110 --> 00:05:58.589
Commit to Jehovah whatever you do

00:05:58.589 --> 00:06:00.790
and your plans will succeed.

00:06:01.790 --> 00:06:05.310
The team was also encouraged to think outside the box,

00:06:05.310 --> 00:06:07.310
which means to think outside or beyond

00:06:07.310 --> 00:06:10.509
the way things have always been done in the past.

00:06:10.509 --> 00:06:13.550
Times have changed, people have changed,

00:06:13.550 --> 00:06:16.589
and the way that many prefer to be taught has changed.

00:06:17.550 --> 00:06:20.269
These days, they respond better to multimedia

00:06:20.269 --> 00:06:22.550
that engages them and holds their attention.

00:06:24.069 --> 00:06:25.910
The team has shown a puzzle

00:06:26.029 --> 00:06:29.470
that illustrates what it means to think outside the box,

00:06:29.470 --> 00:06:31.550
the nine dots puzzle.

00:06:31.550 --> 00:06:34.310
The challenge is to connect all nine dots

00:06:34.310 --> 00:06:36.709
with just four straight lines.

00:06:36.709 --> 00:06:40.350
Here are a few examples of how some will try to solve the puzzle.

00:06:40.350 --> 00:06:43.870
Notice that with each attempt, one dot is missed.

00:06:43.870 --> 00:06:46.709
The problem is that our mind tends to build a box

00:06:46.709 --> 00:06:49.110
around the dots, and that instantly limits

00:06:49.110 --> 00:06:50.230
what we can imagine.

00:06:51.029 --> 00:06:53.949
The only way to connect all nine dots

00:06:53.949 --> 00:06:58.189
with just four straight lines is by going outside the box

00:06:58.189 --> 00:07:03.500
and thinking differently than we normally would.

00:07:03.500 --> 00:07:06.420
The point was to show that novel, creative thinking

00:07:06.420 --> 00:07:08.500
was needed to imagine something

00:07:08.500 --> 00:07:11.660
other than the traditional way of studying the Bible with people.

00:07:12.500 --> 00:07:14.939
With Jehovah's Spirit guiding, fresh thinking,

00:07:14.939 --> 00:07:17.620
it would be interesting to see what innovative ideas

00:07:17.620 --> 00:07:21.019
could be thought of on how to teach the truth to Bible students.

00:07:21.980 --> 00:07:23.980
And yet it was felt that our brothers and sisters

00:07:23.980 --> 00:07:27.300
would need to see some familiar features in the new publication.

00:07:28.259 --> 00:07:30.740
That's why the first part of each lesson is designed

00:07:30.740 --> 00:07:32.980
similar to the Good News brochure.

00:07:32.980 --> 00:07:37.139
It features numbered questions, each followed by a paragraph

00:07:37.139 --> 00:07:39.939
that briefly covers fundamental facts about the topic.

00:07:40.939 --> 00:07:44.379
Next, the dig deeper section, Reasons on the Topic,

00:07:44.379 --> 00:07:46.459
shows how to apply what's learned

00:07:46.459 --> 00:07:50.379
and discusses what the topic teaches us about Jehovah.

00:07:50.379 --> 00:07:54.259
It includes features found in the Life and Ministry meeting workbook,

00:07:54.259 --> 00:07:58.500
bolleted discussion points, scriptures to read, videos to play,

00:07:58.500 --> 00:08:00.500
and viewpoint questions to answer.

00:08:01.540 --> 00:08:03.939
And like the study articles in the Watch Tower,

00:08:03.939 --> 00:08:08.660
the last part of each lesson includes just three review questions.

00:08:08.660 --> 00:08:12.100
It was decided that we could cover much less printed material

00:08:12.100 --> 00:08:14.100
and let the Bible do the teaching.

00:08:14.980 --> 00:08:17.259
That we need to draw out the student's feelings

00:08:17.259 --> 00:08:19.899
with well-worded viewpoint questions

00:08:19.899 --> 00:08:22.100
and include videos in generous artwork.

00:08:23.579 --> 00:08:27.500
We must help the student to see Jehovah as a real person

00:08:27.500 --> 00:08:30.540
and to develop a warm relationship with him

00:08:30.540 --> 00:08:33.100
and encourage the student to get into a routine

00:08:33.100 --> 00:08:36.220
or regular Bible reading prayer and meeting attendance.

00:08:37.179 --> 00:08:39.940
Does enjoy life forever provide what we need

00:08:39.940 --> 00:08:41.980
to accomplish all of that?

00:08:41.980 --> 00:08:44.100
It certainly does.

00:08:44.139 --> 00:08:47.779
The scriptures are the focal point of each lesson.

00:08:47.779 --> 00:08:50.860
So the student is prompted to find answers in the Bible.

00:08:51.779 --> 00:08:53.940
The questions draw out the student's feelings

00:08:53.940 --> 00:08:56.019
about what he's learning.

00:08:56.019 --> 00:08:58.820
Early in the course, students are helped to appreciate

00:08:58.820 --> 00:09:03.419
what Jehovah is like, to feel his love for them

00:09:03.419 --> 00:09:07.100
and to see how to draw close to him as their friend.

00:09:07.100 --> 00:09:09.620
The beautiful artwork and motivating videos

00:09:09.620 --> 00:09:11.659
have real emotional impact.

00:09:12.659 --> 00:09:16.019
This project to produce enjoy life forever

00:09:16.019 --> 00:09:18.700
require the collaboration of six departments

00:09:18.700 --> 00:09:20.700
at World Headquarters.

00:09:20.700 --> 00:09:22.700
As directed by the governing body,

00:09:22.700 --> 00:09:25.019
the writing department researched,

00:09:25.019 --> 00:09:28.659
wrote, and proofread the text for each lesson.

00:09:28.659 --> 00:09:30.500
These were then sent to hundreds of brothers

00:09:30.500 --> 00:09:32.820
and sisters around the world to test them

00:09:32.820 --> 00:09:34.220
on their Bible studies.

00:09:34.980 --> 00:09:37.419
The writing department coordinated the work

00:09:37.419 --> 00:09:40.659
with other departments to keep the project on schedule.

00:09:41.820 --> 00:09:45.340
Translation services helped to simplify the vocabulary

00:09:45.340 --> 00:09:47.779
and logic of what was written.

00:09:47.779 --> 00:09:51.059
They identified any English text that would be a problem

00:09:51.059 --> 00:09:53.820
for translators to render in their local languages.

00:09:54.740 --> 00:09:57.899
As of right now, enjoy life forever has been approved

00:09:57.899 --> 00:10:00.580
and upward of 700 languages.

00:10:01.539 --> 00:10:04.700
The art department designed the book's layout and artwork.

00:10:05.620 --> 00:10:08.100
Teams and several branches photograph models

00:10:08.100 --> 00:10:11.500
to help the illustrators create the many beautiful scenes

00:10:11.500 --> 00:10:16.139
that appear in the book, which contains over 600 images.

00:10:16.139 --> 00:10:18.139
Maps programming developed new tools

00:10:18.139 --> 00:10:20.100
so that the digital version of the book

00:10:20.100 --> 00:10:25.100
in the JW Library app would look similar to the printed edition.

00:10:25.299 --> 00:10:27.019
This was the first publication

00:10:27.019 --> 00:10:29.500
for which both print and digital formats

00:10:29.500 --> 00:10:31.299
were designed simultaneously.

00:10:32.340 --> 00:10:35.740
Text processing services composed the text and artwork

00:10:35.740 --> 00:10:38.139
for both the print and digital formats,

00:10:38.139 --> 00:10:40.659
transcribed the book into English Braille

00:10:40.659 --> 00:10:43.259
and instructed the branches on how to produce the book

00:10:43.259 --> 00:10:45.139
in their languages.

00:10:45.139 --> 00:10:47.980
Audio video services produced several new videos

00:10:47.980 --> 00:10:50.779
and excerpts of many existing videos

00:10:50.779 --> 00:10:53.340
from the JW.org website.

00:10:53.340 --> 00:10:56.139
They also produced unique audio recordings

00:10:56.139 --> 00:10:59.299
of the book that include various voices and sounds.

00:11:00.340 --> 00:11:02.460
This was truly a collaborative effort,

00:11:03.259 --> 00:11:07.220
but there was a major problem that could have stalled this project,

00:11:07.220 --> 00:11:08.539
COVID-19.

00:11:09.539 --> 00:11:13.059
When World Headquarters and the branches were locked down,

00:11:13.059 --> 00:11:16.899
60% of the project still needed to be completed,

00:11:16.899 --> 00:11:19.899
and yet the governing body had given it high priority.

00:11:21.179 --> 00:11:23.419
The following video will give you some idea

00:11:23.419 --> 00:11:25.980
of how the departments worked together

00:11:25.980 --> 00:11:29.379
to get their work done despite the challenges they faced

00:11:29.379 --> 00:11:30.740
during the pandemic.

00:11:31.620 --> 00:11:33.779
Everything about enjoy life forever is different

00:11:33.779 --> 00:11:36.580
from any other publication we've produced in the past

00:11:36.740 --> 00:11:39.139
and from the start of the project, two things were critical,

00:11:39.139 --> 00:11:42.059
good communication and good documentation.

00:11:42.059 --> 00:11:44.139
But honestly, time and again, the thing that proved

00:11:44.139 --> 00:11:46.740
to be the most important was reliance on Jehovah.

00:11:46.740 --> 00:11:49.500
The writing committee's goal was to create a first-class

00:11:49.500 --> 00:11:53.620
digital experience that would engage Bible students.

00:11:53.620 --> 00:11:57.019
The digital design system had to be completely remodeled

00:11:57.019 --> 00:11:59.299
so that enjoy life forever would look uniform,

00:11:59.299 --> 00:12:04.100
whether it's viewed in JW Library on JW.org or in print.

00:12:04.100 --> 00:12:06.419
Right from the inception of this project,

00:12:06.419 --> 00:12:08.740
the brothers looked for inputs of a study material

00:12:08.740 --> 00:12:12.500
would be easily available in as many languages as possible.

00:12:12.500 --> 00:12:15.700
And for that reason, a team from translation services

00:12:15.700 --> 00:12:17.139
worked along with the writers.

00:12:18.019 --> 00:12:20.299
A publication of this size would usually take

00:12:20.299 --> 00:12:22.620
about two or three years to complete,

00:12:22.620 --> 00:12:24.500
but the writing committee was really interested

00:12:24.500 --> 00:12:26.299
in getting the enjoy life forever book

00:12:26.299 --> 00:12:28.179
out there as soon as possible.

00:12:28.179 --> 00:12:30.299
The enjoy life forever book required an intense

00:12:30.299 --> 00:12:31.580
amount of collaboration.

00:12:31.580 --> 00:12:33.419
Right from the beginning, the writing committee

00:12:33.419 --> 00:12:35.220
got all six departments together

00:12:35.220 --> 00:12:37.539
so we could work in idly through their production.

00:12:38.539 --> 00:12:41.580
Enjoy life forever has many elements.

00:12:41.580 --> 00:12:45.580
Over 250 pages of text, 597 images,

00:12:48.340 --> 00:12:53.340
121 video boxes, 840 links, and 62 QR codes.

00:12:56.860 --> 00:13:01.700
Also, the goal box must allow the student to add text

00:13:01.820 --> 00:13:05.220
and we had to build alternate layouts for languages

00:13:05.220 --> 00:13:08.139
that have longer text and for languages

00:13:08.139 --> 00:13:10.019
that read right to the end.

00:13:11.460 --> 00:13:13.940
Our existing toolset didn't have the ability

00:13:13.940 --> 00:13:17.500
to style digital publications like we can with print.

00:13:17.500 --> 00:13:21.379
We could do black text on a white background with gray boxes.

00:13:21.379 --> 00:13:23.220
That was the extent of the functionality

00:13:23.220 --> 00:13:24.379
that we had available.

00:13:25.220 --> 00:13:28.460
And joy life forever is very interactive for the student.

00:13:28.460 --> 00:13:30.860
When producing the audio for this publication,

00:13:30.860 --> 00:13:33.340
we endeavor to maintain that feel.

00:13:33.340 --> 00:13:36.860
So we added multiple voices, musical cues,

00:13:36.860 --> 00:13:39.700
and in some cases, the audio track for the video

00:13:39.700 --> 00:13:42.580
was re-edited to teach the point effectively.

00:13:42.580 --> 00:13:44.460
When we got to Lesson 32,

00:13:44.460 --> 00:13:46.580
we felt that it might be too complicated

00:13:46.580 --> 00:13:48.940
to build as a digital experience,

00:13:48.940 --> 00:13:51.580
but that's when the collaboration really paid off.

00:13:51.580 --> 00:13:53.980
It took every tool that we had,

00:13:53.980 --> 00:13:55.940
and basically every trick in order

00:13:55.940 --> 00:13:58.580
to build the digital version of that lesson.

00:13:58.580 --> 00:14:00.259
As we were working on the prototype,

00:14:00.259 --> 00:14:02.659
we would collaborate with the user experience group

00:14:02.659 --> 00:14:05.299
to make sure that the look and feel of the digital addition

00:14:05.299 --> 00:14:06.139
was the same,

00:14:06.139 --> 00:14:09.419
whether it was on a large device or a small device.

00:14:09.419 --> 00:14:11.700
The entire chart is a visual aid.

00:14:11.700 --> 00:14:13.700
So we wanted to be sure that all of our users,

00:14:13.700 --> 00:14:15.820
especially those who are visually impaired,

00:14:15.820 --> 00:14:18.580
would be able to understand the teaching point.

00:14:18.580 --> 00:14:20.580
This required us to build the chart

00:14:20.580 --> 00:14:23.100
so that screen readers could read the text

00:14:23.100 --> 00:14:25.340
and that each picture would have a description

00:14:25.340 --> 00:14:26.379
for those who needed it.

00:14:27.460 --> 00:14:28.899
Early in the concept stage,

00:14:28.899 --> 00:14:31.139
we understood that there would be about 200 videos

00:14:31.139 --> 00:14:34.580
in this publication requiring thousands of hours of work.

00:14:34.580 --> 00:14:37.460
Eight brand new videos of the remaining videos

00:14:37.460 --> 00:14:40.139
around 60 would need to be edited.

00:14:40.139 --> 00:14:41.820
Just as the eight new videos were entering

00:14:41.820 --> 00:14:44.860
the production phase, COVID-19 hit,

00:14:44.860 --> 00:14:48.139
effectively halting video production around the world.

